How to protect the rights of unfinished buildings according to law?
On October 10, an announcement showed that Tao Moumou, an owner of Yufeng Garden in Baoding City, Hebei Province, was taken criminal compulsory measures for allegedly inciting owners to petition in Beijing, and 15 other people were taken administrative compulsory measures
It is reported that the government originally promised to hand over the house on December 31, 2023, but as of now, the house has not been started, so the owners decided to petition. As a result, they were arrested on the grounds of "having a clear plan and using petitions to exert pressure"
